Package com.ibm.streams.management.job

Interface OperatorOutputPortMXBean

All Superinterfaces:
OperatorPortMXBean
public interface OperatorOutputPortMXBean extends OperatorPortMXBean
OperatorOutputPortMXBean provides attributes, operations, and notifications for managing an operator output port of a Streams job.

Note: The job must be registered before accessing any of these attributes or operations. See InstanceMXBean.registerJob(BigInteger) for more information.

ObjectNameBuilder.operatorOutputPort(String, String, BigInteger, String, int) can be used to build the ObjectName for a OperatorOutputPortMXBean.

Notifications:
A OperatorOutputPortMXBean supports sending the following notifications:

Notifications.OPERATOR_OUTPUT_PORT_EXPORT_PROPERTIES_CHANGED

Notification categories:
These categories can be used with notification filters to easily filter out all notifications in a category.
Notifications.OPERATOR_NOTIFICATION

    • retrieveStreamType

      String retrieveStreamType()
      Returns an HTTPS URI to retrieve the tuple type information for the stream associated with the output port.
      Returns:
      an HTTPS URI to access the stream type information in application/json format. This URI is valid for a single access for up to two minutes.

      The stream type information is provided in JSON format with an array tupleAttributes parameter. Each item in the tupleAttributes array has the format described in the product documentation. See topic: REST management API reference > Get operator output port. The following differences exist for the JMX output:

      • The REST specific properties: next, previous, total, and resourceType are not included.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the operation is unable to complete successfully.
      SecurityException - if the current user does not have the required permissions to perform the operation. Information about Streams permissions can be found in the product documentation. See topic: Security objects for Teracloud Streams domains and instances.
